      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Combine the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>peri-peri spice mix </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>in a large bowl and set aside – this is your <strong>marinated chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681817558778-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681817558778-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
